HCR 53 Original 2026 Regular Session Schamerhorn
Establishes a study committee to examine oversized vehicle permits issued by political
subdivisions and related impacts, including the economic effects of such permits, all taxes
and fees paid for local highways, and permitting practices in neighboring states. Requires
the study committee meet on a monthly or bi-monthly basis during the moratorium period
to evaluate current permitting processes and their impacts and submit a written report
detailing its findings and recommendations to the speaker of the House of Representatives
and the president of the Senate by Feb. 1, 2027.
